President Obama has announced over 300 private and public sector commitments to advance solar deployment and energy efficiency. These commitments represent over 850 megawatts of solar deployed and energy efficiency investments that will lower bills for more than 1 billion square feet of buildings. The President also announced new executive actions that will lead to $2 billion in energy efficiency investments in Federal buildings, smarter appliances that will cut carbon pollution by over 380 million metric tons, and training programs at community colleges to assist 50,000 workers to enter the solar industry by 2020. These actions and commitments aim to create jobs, cut carbon pollution, and promote clean energy.